{
  "sourceText": "Each run lives in its own git worktree. That means parallel runs never collide with each other. worca builds on this with two scale-out modes. The first is fleet mode. It takes one prompt and runs it across many independent projects at the same time. That's perfect for rolling a fix across every repo you own. The second is workspace mode. This one is for interdependent projects. A master planner figures out the dependency order. Child pipelines run tier by tier. And between tiers, worca runs cross-project integration tests to keep everything in sync.",
